snippet: Cole Hamels pitched a three-hitter, Adrian Beltre hit a go-ahead homer and the Rangers beat the visiting Angels, 9-2, on Sunday, eliminating Los Angeles from playoff contention.
abstract: Baseball Roundup; Texas Rangers defeat Los Angeles Angels, 9-2, to clinch American League West title; other MLB scores noted.
lead_paragraph: Cole Hamels pitched a three-hitter, Adrian Beltre hit a go-ahead homer and the Rangers beat the visiting Angels, 9-2, on Sunday, eliminating Los Angeles from playoff contention.

headline.print_headline: In Their Third Opportunity, Rangers Wrap Up A.L. West
headline.main: In Their Third Opportunity, Rangers Wrap Up A.L. West
